class Animal{ //parent or super
	void eat()
}
class Dog extends Animal{ //child or sub-class
	void eat()
}

  - when an object acquires all the properties and behaviours of a parent object
  - provides code re-usability
  - represents IS-A relationship
  eg. Dog is a animal,
      Cat is a animal,
      Sparrow is a bird
      Doctor is a person

Types of Inheritance
a) Single Inheritance -
b) Multilevel Inheritance -
c) Hierarchical Inheritance -
d) Multiple Inheritance
	- Java does not support multiple inheritance
	- Ambiguity problem
class A{
	void show(){
	}
}
class B {
	void show(){
	}
}
class C extends B,A{//Ambiguity problem
}
class Impl{
	main(){
	 C c = new C();
	 c.show();
	}
}





e) Hybrid Inheritance


